<subSubSection id="C36A6504A46BFFADFF58F89BFC25FD84" pageId="10" pageNumber="299" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCF368FA46BFFADFF58F89BFC25FD84" blockId="10.[136,786,1857,1946]" lastBlockId="10.[824,1476,279,530]" pageId="10" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46BFFADFF58F89BFF61F8CF" box="[174,240,1858,1881]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="299">Notes.</emphasis>
– This species was described from 
<collectingCountry id="F367761FA46BFFADFD7AF898FEF9F8EC" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="10" pageNumber="299">Democratic Republic of Congo</collectingCountry>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE14B7EA46BFFADFE5CF8BBFD1DF8EC" author="VERDCOURT" box="[426,652,1890,1914]" firstAuthor="VERDCOURT" pageId="10" pageNumber="299" pagination="785 - 818" refId="ref27689" refString="VERDCOURT, B. (1977). A synopsis of the genus Chazaliella (Rubiaceae-Psychotrieae). Kew Bull. 31: 785 - 818." type="journal article" year="1977">VERDCOURT (1977)</bibRefCitation>
considered it poorly known. He noted that it is apparently similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46BFFADFCCEFECEFC64FEB9" authorityName="Razafim. &amp; C. M. Taylor" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Razafim. &amp; C. M. Taylor" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[824,1013,279,303]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Eumachia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="10" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oddonii">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46BFFADFCCEFECEFC64FEB9" box="[824,1013,279,303]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="299">Eumachia oddonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and may even be the same in which case the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46BFFADFC55FEE1FB91FED9" box="[931,1024,312,335]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Margaritopsis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="10" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="poggei">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46BFFADFC55FEE1FB91FED9" box="[931,1024,312,335]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="299">E. poggei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has priority over 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46BFFADFB4AFEE1FAB7FED9" authorityName="Razafim. &amp; C. M. Taylor" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="Razafim. &amp; C. M. Taylor" baseAuthorityYear="2017" box="[1212,1318,311,335]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Eumachia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="10" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oddonii">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46BFFADFB4AFEE1FAB7FED9" box="[1212,1318,311,335]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="299">E. oddonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both of these names are provisionally accepted here following VERDCOURT. 
<taxonomicName id="4C704D0CA46BFFADFCCEFEA1FC61FE06" box="[824,1008,376,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Psychotria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="10" pageNumber="299" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="poggei">
<emphasis id="B904EA9DA46BFFADFCCEFEA1FC61FE06" box="[824,1008,376,400]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="299">Psychotria poggei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on several 
<typeStatus id="54CB882DA46BFFADFA94FEA0FA50FE07" box="[1378,1473,377,401]" pageId="10" pageNumber="299">syntypes</typeStatus>
that were deposited at B and have since been destroyed. No duplicates of these have so far been located, so further study is needed before the typification and identity of this name can be resolved.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
